WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:18.779 align:middle line:90%


00:00:18.779 --> 00:00:21.320 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA GARR: Hi, I'm Lisa Garr,
host of "Gaiam Inspirations."

00:00:21.320 --> 00:00:23.560 align:middle line:10%
And we are coming to you
live from the Gaiam studios

00:00:23.560 --> 00:00:24.930 align:middle line:10%
here in Boulder, Colorado.

00:00:24.930 --> 00:00:27.052 align:middle line:10%
And since this is a
live interactive show

00:00:27.052 --> 00:00:28.510 align:middle line:10%
I encourage you to
interact with us

00:00:28.510 --> 00:00:30.280 align:middle line:10%
through Facebook and Twitter.

00:00:30.280 --> 00:00:32.940 align:middle line:10%
Many of you already have, so
keep the comments and questions

00:00:32.940 --> 00:00:34.570 align:middle line:10%
coming throughout the show.

00:00:34.570 --> 00:00:37.930 align:middle line:10%
So with all of the challenges
that are going on in the world,

00:00:37.930 --> 00:00:40.370 align:middle line:10%
where do we even find
a place in our lives

00:00:40.370 --> 00:00:42.880 align:middle line:10%
to have a conversation
about enlightenment?

00:00:42.880 --> 00:00:45.730 align:middle line:84%
And what is the difference
between self-awareness

00:00:45.730 --> 00:00:46.730 align:middle line:90%
and narcissism?

00:00:46.730 --> 00:00:48.335 align:middle line:90%
Can we be too self-aware?

00:00:48.335 --> 00:00:51.290 align:middle line:84%
Can we be so wrapped up
in our own complaints

00:00:51.290 --> 00:00:54.550 align:middle line:84%
that we don't look at the
bigger picture of why we exist?

00:00:54.550 --> 00:00:58.320 align:middle line:84%
Joining me today is spiritual
teacher and cultural visionary

00:00:58.320 --> 00:00:59.140 align:middle line:90%
Andrew Cohen.

00:00:59.140 --> 00:01:01.010 align:middle line:84%
And he's here to talk
about his new book,

00:01:01.010 --> 00:01:04.707 align:middle line:84%
"Evolutionary Enlightment- A New
Path to Spiritual Awakening."

00:01:04.707 --> 00:01:06.290 align:middle line:84%
And he's going to
talk to us about how

00:01:06.290 --> 00:01:09.144 align:middle line:84%
to achieve enlightenment in
the midst of all of our chaos.

00:01:09.144 --> 00:01:11.060 align:middle line:84%
Welcome to the show,
thank you for being here.

00:01:11.060 --> 00:01:11.410 align:middle line:90%
>>ANDREW COHEN: Hi, Lisa.

00:01:11.410 --> 00:01:12.870 align:middle line:90%
It's a thrill to be with you.

00:01:12.870 --> 00:01:15.170 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's great, and an
honor to have you with us.

00:01:15.170 --> 00:01:17.980 align:middle line:84%
So why do you think that
people even seek enlightenment

00:01:17.980 --> 00:01:18.780 align:middle line:90%
in the first place?

00:01:18.780 --> 00:01:19.829 align:middle line:90%
What are we looking for?

00:01:19.829 --> 00:01:21.620 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, there's
a couple of reasons.

00:01:21.620 --> 00:01:23.975 align:middle line:84%
Number one, I think people
get tired of suffering.

00:01:23.975 --> 00:01:25.030 align:middle line:10%
>>LISA: So tired of pain?

00:01:25.030 --> 00:01:27.120 align:middle line:10%
>>COHEN: They get tired
of pain and suffering.

00:01:27.120 --> 00:01:30.230 align:middle line:10%
Also, I think sensitive,
thoughtful people

00:01:30.230 --> 00:01:33.030 align:middle line:10%
want to have a
breakthrough where there's

00:01:33.030 --> 00:01:35.860 align:middle line:10%
a sense of actually being rooted
in something deeper than just

00:01:35.860 --> 00:01:37.260 align:middle line:10%
their ego.

00:01:37.260 --> 00:01:39.500 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yes, and that's
where that question comes in,

00:01:39.500 --> 00:01:43.850 align:middle line:84%
is what's the difference between
self-awareness and narcissism?

00:01:43.850 --> 00:01:46.750 align:middle line:84%
I mean, can we be
too self-aware?

00:01:46.750 --> 00:01:49.085 align:middle line:84%
Can we be too caught
up in ourselves

00:01:49.085 --> 00:01:51.547 align:middle line:90%
to even see the bigger picture?

00:01:51.547 --> 00:01:52.630 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: Well, definitely.

00:01:52.630 --> 00:01:54.421 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I think there's
a cultural epidemic

00:01:54.421 --> 00:01:56.000 align:middle line:90%
in our day of narcissism.

00:01:56.000 --> 00:02:00.020 align:middle line:84%
And a narcissist is someone who
is compulsively self-concerned.

00:02:00.020 --> 00:02:01.690 align:middle line:84%
Always thinking
about oneself, always

00:02:01.690 --> 00:02:03.124 align:middle line:84%
thinking about
himself or herself.

00:02:03.124 --> 00:02:05.540 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's what we were
taught to do though, isn't it?

00:02:05.540 --> 00:02:07.730 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, we live in
a culture of narcissism.

00:02:07.730 --> 00:02:09.630 align:middle line:84%
We live in a
culture of flattery.

00:02:09.630 --> 00:02:12.790 align:middle line:84%
And we tend to learn, I
think at a very early age

00:02:12.790 --> 00:02:15.290 align:middle line:84%
these days, to always
be looking at ourselves

00:02:15.290 --> 00:02:17.500 align:middle line:90%
in the mirror of our own mind.

00:02:17.500 --> 00:02:21.781 align:middle line:84%
And this can be emotionally and
spiritually quite suffocating.

00:02:21.781 --> 00:02:23.530 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It was a bit
of a backlash though,

00:02:23.530 --> 00:02:24.196 align:middle line:90%
don't you think?

00:02:24.196 --> 00:02:29.045 align:middle line:84%
Because now you get a trophy
for just playing a soccer game,

00:02:29.045 --> 00:02:31.620 align:middle line:84%
you don't have to
actually win anything

00:02:31.620 --> 00:02:32.880 align:middle line:90%
to get the trophy these days.

00:02:32.880 --> 00:02:33.870 align:middle line:90%
I mean, it was--

00:02:33.870 --> 00:02:36.190 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: You mean we get a
prize just because we exist.

00:02:36.190 --> 00:02:37.720 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Right, we get
a prize for existing.

00:02:37.720 --> 00:02:38.680 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Not because
we've necessarily

00:02:38.680 --> 00:02:39.870 align:middle line:90%
achieved something great.

00:02:39.870 --> 00:02:43.270 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What's that
a backlash from?

00:02:43.270 --> 00:02:44.890 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, I
think this has to do

00:02:44.890 --> 00:02:49.210 align:middle line:84%
with the emergence of what's
called the sensitive self.

00:02:49.210 --> 00:02:53.220 align:middle line:84%
Especially in the
1960s, the mere fact

00:02:53.220 --> 00:02:55.880 align:middle line:84%
that we existed as
a sensitive, feeling

00:02:55.880 --> 00:02:59.950 align:middle line:84%
being was seen as having
great value in and of itself.

00:02:59.950 --> 00:03:04.450 align:middle line:84%
And the whole notion of merit
and of having to earn something

00:03:04.450 --> 00:03:09.830 align:middle line:84%
and to develop started to take
a second place to the sense

00:03:09.830 --> 00:03:12.980 align:middle line:84%
of we're special simply
because we exist.

00:03:12.980 --> 00:03:15.890 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So in the concept of
Evolutionary Enlightenment,

00:03:15.890 --> 00:03:16.440 align:middle line:90%
what is that?

00:03:16.440 --> 00:03:17.692 align:middle line:90%
What does that mean?

00:03:17.692 --> 00:03:19.900 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, that's putting
the traditional Eastern

00:03:19.900 --> 00:03:22.320 align:middle line:84%
notion of enlightenment--
and enlightenment

00:03:22.320 --> 00:03:23.950 align:middle line:84%
means the experience
of consciousness

00:03:23.950 --> 00:03:26.670 align:middle line:84%
beyond ego, or beyond
the small self--

00:03:26.670 --> 00:03:31.140 align:middle line:84%
in the context of our emerging
understanding of evolution

00:03:31.140 --> 00:03:33.270 align:middle line:90%
that's based on Western science.

00:03:33.270 --> 00:03:37.660 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And you have been a
seeker of enlightenment pretty

00:03:37.660 --> 00:03:39.640 align:middle line:84%
much since your teenage
years, and now are

00:03:39.640 --> 00:03:43.250 align:middle line:84%
a teacher of this
vast, vast concept.

00:03:43.250 --> 00:03:45.930 align:middle line:84%
Can you tell us a little
bit about how you started

00:03:45.930 --> 00:03:49.820 align:middle line:84%
and what questions
did you ask when

00:03:49.820 --> 00:03:53.380 align:middle line:84%
you were young to seek
this enlightenment?

00:03:53.380 --> 00:03:57.100 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, for me I had an
extraordinary experience when

00:03:57.100 --> 00:03:59.760 align:middle line:84%
I was a young person that
revealed to me that there's

00:03:59.760 --> 00:04:03.870 align:middle line:84%
much more going on here than
I had previously imagined.

00:04:03.870 --> 00:04:06.536 align:middle line:84%
I experienced, as
many teenagers do,

00:04:06.536 --> 00:04:08.910 align:middle line:84%
I had an experience of what's
called cosmic consciousness

00:04:08.910 --> 00:04:12.430 align:middle line:84%
when I was a young person that
really knocked me for a loop.

00:04:12.430 --> 00:04:15.640 align:middle line:84%
I had an experience
of beginninglessness

00:04:15.640 --> 00:04:16.850 align:middle line:90%
and endlessness.

00:04:16.850 --> 00:04:19.610 align:middle line:84%
An awareness of the
infinite, the whole universe

00:04:19.610 --> 00:04:22.320 align:middle line:84%
came alive in my own
mind and consciousness

00:04:22.320 --> 00:04:24.570 align:middle line:90%
for a few moments one evening.

00:04:24.570 --> 00:04:27.720 align:middle line:84%
And those few moments, I
realize, were more real

00:04:27.720 --> 00:04:30.190 align:middle line:84%
and I was more alive than
I'd ever been in my life.

00:04:30.190 --> 00:04:32.490 align:middle line:84%
So when I eventually
became a seeker

00:04:32.490 --> 00:04:35.030 align:middle line:84%
when I was in my
early 20s, it was

00:04:35.030 --> 00:04:37.540 align:middle line:84%
to rediscover what
had spontaneously

00:04:37.540 --> 00:04:38.870 align:middle line:90%
occurred when I was a teenager.

00:04:38.870 --> 00:04:41.036 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you were trying
to get back to that split

00:04:41.036 --> 00:04:42.180 align:middle line:90%
second moment you had.

00:04:42.180 --> 00:04:44.792 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Yes, I was trying to
rediscover those few moments

00:04:44.792 --> 00:04:47.250 align:middle line:84%
in my life that I had no doubt
were more real than anything

00:04:47.250 --> 00:04:48.346 align:middle line:90%
else I'd ever experienced.

00:04:48.346 --> 00:04:49.970 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Was that
complete total freedom

00:04:49.970 --> 00:04:52.180 align:middle line:90%
that you had in that moment?

00:04:52.180 --> 00:04:56.710 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: It was perfect freedom.

00:04:56.710 --> 00:04:58.890 align:middle line:84%
There was freedom from
self-consciousness--

00:04:58.890 --> 00:05:00.530 align:middle line:84%
we've been talking
about narcissism.

00:05:00.530 --> 00:05:03.900 align:middle line:84%
There was total freedom
from self-consciousness.

00:05:03.900 --> 00:05:07.810 align:middle line:84%
And there was an experience
of the inherent goodness

00:05:07.810 --> 00:05:10.790 align:middle line:84%
in the universe and
existence itself.

00:05:10.790 --> 00:05:12.480 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: We have a
clip here of something

00:05:12.480 --> 00:05:15.540 align:middle line:84%
called Kosmocentric
Orientation You can kind of get

00:05:15.540 --> 00:05:17.070 align:middle line:90%
a glimpse into Andrew's world.

00:05:17.070 --> 00:05:19.758 align:middle line:90%
Take a look at this.

00:05:19.758 --> 00:05:27.550 align:middle line:10%
