>>COHEN: Yeah.

00:07:14.070 --> 00:07:15.300 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I love that.

00:07:15.300 --> 00:07:18.180 align:middle line:84%
So questions are coming in
from our Facebook listeners.

00:07:18.180 --> 00:07:21.390 align:middle line:84%
Dante's asking, how do I
move on a day to day basis

00:07:21.390 --> 00:07:23.216 align:middle line:90%
beyond the ego?

00:07:23.216 --> 00:07:25.090 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, the way
to move beyond the ego

00:07:25.090 --> 00:07:30.707 align:middle line:84%
is we have to want to
evolve beyond our own ego.

00:07:30.707 --> 00:07:32.540 align:middle line:84%
We have to cultivate a
very big and profound

00:07:32.540 --> 00:07:35.570 align:middle line:84%
spiritual aspiration
to want to rise up,

00:07:35.570 --> 00:07:38.490 align:middle line:84%
way up above the place
we've been living

00:07:38.490 --> 00:07:40.580 align:middle line:84%
in our own mind and
emotions for a long time.

00:07:40.580 --> 00:07:43.030 align:middle line:84%
We have to really
want to be free.

00:07:43.030 --> 00:07:44.097 align:middle line:90%
Really want to be free.

00:07:44.097 --> 00:07:44.930 align:middle line:90%
You want to be free.

00:07:44.930 --> 00:07:46.940 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, what does
that mean to be free?

00:07:46.940 --> 00:07:49.765 align:middle line:84%
And aren't we all
living to survive?

00:07:49.765 --> 00:07:51.640 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, we might
be living to survive.

00:07:51.640 --> 00:07:54.730 align:middle line:84%
But the fears and desires
of the small self,

00:07:54.730 --> 00:07:57.130 align:middle line:84%
once we transcend them, we
realize they're very small.

00:07:57.130 --> 00:07:59.540 align:middle line:84%
It's a very small little
place emotionally,

00:07:59.540 --> 00:08:02.130 align:middle line:84%
psychologically,
philosophically.

00:08:02.130 --> 00:08:04.600 align:middle line:84%
It's a very small
little-- it's like living

00:08:04.600 --> 00:08:07.540 align:middle line:84%
in a little tiny
cave all by oneself.

00:08:07.540 --> 00:08:11.240 align:middle line:84%
And when you transcend
it, you realize

00:08:11.240 --> 00:08:14.256 align:middle line:84%
that one was living in a
prison without even knowing it.

00:08:14.256 --> 00:08:15.630 align:middle line:84%
The thing is, the
prison can feel

00:08:15.630 --> 00:08:17.213 align:middle line:84%
very safe and
comfortable because it's

00:08:17.213 --> 00:08:19.520 align:middle line:84%
what's usually very
familiar to us.

00:08:19.520 --> 00:08:22.260 align:middle line:84%
So we have to be willing to want
to leave that which is familiar

00:08:22.260 --> 00:08:25.780 align:middle line:84%
so we can experience the
enormous freedom that's

00:08:25.780 --> 00:08:27.150 align:middle line:90%
on the other side of that.

00:08:27.150 --> 00:08:28.900 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So when you
had that experience,

00:08:28.900 --> 00:08:34.000 align:middle line:84%
and when you have sought out
the teachings of amazing people,

00:08:34.000 --> 00:08:35.539 align:middle line:90%
what is that light?

00:08:35.539 --> 00:08:37.740 align:middle line:84%
Give us a glimpse
into what it means

00:08:37.740 --> 00:08:43.159 align:middle line:84%
to have that limitless complete
sense of enlightenment,

00:08:43.159 --> 00:08:45.190 align:middle line:90%
of freedom.

00:08:45.190 --> 00:08:48.970 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, it's
experiencing a boundarylessness,

00:08:48.970 --> 00:08:52.110 align:middle line:90%
it's a freedom from boundaries.

00:08:52.110 --> 00:08:54.830 align:middle line:84%
It's the awakening to, at
the level of experience,

00:08:54.830 --> 00:08:57.020 align:middle line:84%
that which has no
beginning and no end.

00:08:57.020 --> 00:09:00.790 align:middle line:84%
And simultaneously
recognizing that who you are

00:09:00.790 --> 00:09:04.020 align:middle line:84%
and what we all are is
not separate from that

00:09:04.020 --> 00:09:05.900 align:middle line:84%
which has no
beginning and no end.

00:09:05.900 --> 00:09:09.280 align:middle line:90%
It's birthless and deathless.

00:09:09.280 --> 00:09:12.270 align:middle line:84%
So it's becoming self-aware,
or self-conscious

00:09:12.270 --> 00:09:15.990 align:middle line:84%
of the infinite nature of one's
own being of existence itself.

00:09:15.990 --> 00:09:18.870 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Do you think that
our attachment to things,

00:09:18.870 --> 00:09:23.510 align:middle line:84%
and to people, and
to money separate us

00:09:23.510 --> 00:09:25.679 align:middle line:84%
from that experience
you're talking about?

00:09:25.679 --> 00:09:27.720 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, from an
enlightenment perspective,

00:09:27.720 --> 00:09:30.610 align:middle line:84%
attachment to anything other
than that which is infinite,

00:09:30.610 --> 00:09:32.490 align:middle line:84%
then that which has no
beginning and no end

00:09:32.490 --> 00:09:34.664 align:middle line:90%
is going to cause us to suffer.

00:09:34.664 --> 00:09:36.580 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's going to
cause detachment, right?

00:09:36.580 --> 00:09:38.910 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, it will
cause attachment--

00:09:38.910 --> 00:09:40.000 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Attachment, sorry.

00:09:40.000 --> 00:09:41.541 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: It will
definitely cause it.

00:09:41.541 --> 00:09:43.340 align:middle line:90%
We will suffer.

00:09:43.340 --> 00:09:45.850 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So how do you
separate from that attachment?

00:09:45.850 --> 00:09:49.255 align:middle line:84%
How do you get to a
place of non-attachment?

00:09:49.255 --> 00:09:50.969 align:middle line:84%
It's a Buddhist
philosophy, right?

00:09:50.969 --> 00:09:53.510 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, by coming to that
point in our own development

00:09:53.510 --> 00:09:58.345 align:middle line:84%
where we want that which has
no beginning and no end more

00:09:58.345 --> 00:09:59.470 align:middle line:90%
than we want anything else.

00:09:59.470 --> 00:10:00.560 align:middle line:90%
We want the infinite.

00:10:00.560 --> 00:10:04.020 align:middle line:84%
We want ultimate spirit, the
limitless nature of spirit,

00:10:04.020 --> 00:10:06.600 align:middle line:84%
of reality itself, more
than anything else.

00:10:06.600 --> 00:10:10.420 align:middle line:84%
We want to experience the
intimacy of that which

00:10:10.420 --> 00:10:12.780 align:middle line:84%
is intimate more than
anything else in life.

00:10:12.780 --> 00:10:14.140 align:middle line:90%
That has to come first for us.

00:10:14.140 --> 00:10:19.160 align:middle line:84%
It has to become our absolute
priority before anything else.

00:10:19.160 --> 00:10:24.190 align:middle line:84%
And when we make that
shift, if we can do that,

00:10:24.190 --> 00:10:27.086 align:middle line:84%
it brings so much space
to our relationships,

00:10:27.086 --> 00:10:29.210 align:middle line:84%
to our relationship with
life, because we no longer

00:10:29.210 --> 00:10:32.820 align:middle line:84%
feel bound to people,
places, or things.

00:10:32.820 --> 00:10:36.290 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And so this is what
you call nonduality, right?

00:10:36.290 --> 00:10:41.037 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, nonduality is the
awakening to the ultimate truth

00:10:41.037 --> 00:10:42.620 align:middle line:84%
about the self, and
the ultimate truth

00:10:42.620 --> 00:10:44.230 align:middle line:90%
about the nature of reality.

00:10:44.230 --> 00:10:47.120 align:middle line:84%
And all the great mystics from
all the religious traditions

00:10:47.120 --> 00:10:49.750 align:middle line:84%
in the world all say
that the ultimate truth

00:10:49.750 --> 00:10:52.090 align:middle line:84%
about the nature of reality
and the nature of the self

00:10:52.090 --> 00:10:53.860 align:middle line:84%
is there's only
one, and not two.

00:10:53.860 --> 00:10:57.674 align:middle line:84%
The ultimate truth is that
there's only one, and not two.

00:10:57.674 --> 00:10:59.340 align:middle line:84%
And from an evolutionary
point of view--

00:10:59.340 --> 00:11:00.881 align:middle line:84%
and I'm very interested
in evolution,

00:11:00.881 --> 00:11:03.910 align:middle line:84%
which means we're all really
part and parcel of one

00:11:03.910 --> 00:11:06.650 align:middle line:90%
creative process, right?

00:11:06.650 --> 00:11:08.800 align:middle line:84%
And when we look at
evolution we realize

00:11:08.800 --> 00:11:11.090 align:middle line:84%
that the universe
burst into being

00:11:11.090 --> 00:11:13.310 align:middle line:90%
almost 14 billion years ago.

00:11:13.310 --> 00:11:16.620 align:middle line:84%
And everything that exists
is part of that one process

00:11:16.620 --> 00:11:19.950 align:middle line:84%
that is in progress, that's in
a state of cosmic unfolding.

00:11:19.950 --> 00:11:22.050 align:middle line:84%
And you, and I, and
everybody that's listening,

00:11:22.050 --> 00:11:25.030 align:middle line:84%
we're the eyes and
ears-- as human beings,

00:11:25.030 --> 00:11:27.860 align:middle line:84%
as highly evolved human beings--
we're the eyes and the ears

00:11:27.860 --> 00:11:30.090 align:middle line:84%
and the heart and the mind
of the entire process.

00:11:30.090 --> 00:11:32.900 align:middle line:84%
So it's one process,
and my body,

00:11:32.900 --> 00:11:36.430 align:middle line:84%
my mind, and personality--
as is yours-- is

00:11:36.430 --> 00:11:38.770 align:middle line:84%
an expression and a
manifestation of that one

00:11:38.770 --> 00:11:39.740 align:middle line:90%
process.

00:11:39.740 --> 00:11:41.550 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So how does
that get us into what

00:11:41.550 --> 00:11:45.130 align:middle line:84%
you call evolution, our
future conversation?

00:11:45.130 --> 00:11:47.590 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, when
you awakened evolution,

00:11:47.590 --> 00:11:49.720 align:middle line:84%
evolution is a
moving train, it's

00:11:49.720 --> 00:11:52.580 align:middle line:84%
a process that's
going somewhere new.

00:11:52.580 --> 00:11:54.734 align:middle line:84%
In most of human
history, human beings

00:11:54.734 --> 00:11:56.150 align:middle line:84%
thought that nothing
was changing.

00:11:56.150 --> 00:11:59.430 align:middle line:84%
That the cosmos was static,
that nature was static,

00:11:59.430 --> 00:12:01.920 align:middle line:84%
and that human history
and culture was static.

00:12:01.920 --> 00:12:06.140 align:middle line:84%
But now we realize that
the cosmos is moving.

00:12:06.140 --> 00:12:08.630 align:middle line:84%
That biological
life is evolving.

00:12:08.630 --> 00:12:11.350 align:middle line:84%
And that human consciousness
and culture is moving.

00:12:11.350 --> 00:12:13.800 align:middle line:90%
So we're on a moving train.

00:12:13.800 --> 00:12:16.917 align:middle line:84%
We're part of a developmental
process that's going somewhere.

00:12:16.917 --> 00:12:18.500 align:middle line:84%
And the most exciting
part of all this

00:12:18.500 --> 00:12:21.070 align:middle line:84%
is that our human
creative aspirations,

00:12:21.070 --> 00:12:24.280 align:middle line:84%
our spiritual aspirations,
are an expression

00:12:24.280 --> 00:12:27.436 align:middle line:84%
of the desire in the
universe to evolve,

00:12:27.436 --> 00:12:29.310 align:middle line:84%
and to develop, and to
become more conscious.

00:12:29.310 --> 00:12:31.340 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So that's basically
how to get unstuck,

00:12:31.340 --> 00:12:35.140 align:middle line:84%
is by connecting into
that cosmic creation

00:12:35.140 --> 00:12:36.340 align:middle line:90%
that you're talking about.

00:12:36.340 --> 00:12:37.173 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: Well, sure.

00:12:37.173 --> 00:12:41.290 align:middle line:84%
Because for too many of us
we're living a small little life

00:12:41.290 --> 00:12:43.395 align:middle line:84%
based upon our
psychological personality.

00:12:43.395 --> 00:12:46.292 align:middle line:84%
And when you realize
that who I really am

00:12:46.292 --> 00:12:48.500 align:middle line:84%
is not separate from the
energy and intelligence that

00:12:48.500 --> 00:12:53.360 align:middle line:84%
created the universe and is
creating the universe, that's

00:12:53.360 --> 00:12:55.830 align:middle line:84%
awakening to itself in the
form of this body, mind,

00:12:55.830 --> 00:12:59.400 align:middle line:84%
and personality, our
experience, our sense

00:12:59.400 --> 00:13:01.880 align:middle line:84%
in the direct experience of
what it means to be alive,

00:13:01.880 --> 00:13:03.890 align:middle line:84%
becomes infused
with this awareness

00:13:03.890 --> 00:13:08.960 align:middle line:84%
of this cosmic deep time, big
picture, big history context.

00:13:08.960 --> 00:13:15.940 align:middle line:84%
And so our sense of being
alive grows enormously.

00:13:15.940 --> 00:13:17.930 align:middle line:84%
Life becomes really
big, really big.

00:13:17.930 --> 00:13:19.437 align:middle line:84%
Overwhelmingly big,
thrillingly big.

00:13:19.437 --> 00:13:21.520 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So great question
coming in from Facebook.

00:13:21.520 --> 00:13:24.050 align:middle line:84%
One of our listeners is
saying, if I get this concept,

00:13:24.050 --> 00:13:28.450 align:middle line:84%
how do I relate to others
that aren't interested in this

00:13:28.450 --> 00:13:32.550 align:middle line:84%
or are still in the
place, stuck in the ego?

00:13:32.550 --> 00:13:35.310 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: When you
awakened evolution,

00:13:35.310 --> 00:13:39.790 align:middle line:84%
you experience a
sense of inspiration.

00:13:39.790 --> 00:13:43.875 align:middle line:84%
You feel yourself to be
inspired by the same energy

00:13:43.875 --> 00:13:47.340 align:middle line:84%
and intelligence that caused
the universe to come into being.

00:13:47.340 --> 00:13:51.230 align:middle line:84%
When something came from
nothing, it was one big yes.

00:13:51.230 --> 00:13:53.970 align:middle line:84%
And so when you are
an individual who's

00:13:53.970 --> 00:13:58.190 align:middle line:84%
inspired, are turned on by, or
lit up by the creative process,

00:13:58.190 --> 00:14:02.280 align:middle line:84%
other people are drawn to you
because you become a living

00:14:02.280 --> 00:14:06.610 align:middle line:84%
expression and manifestation
of the inherent positivity

00:14:06.610 --> 00:14:08.420 align:middle line:84%
that is driving
this cosmic process.

00:14:08.420 --> 00:14:10.610 align:middle line:84%
So you become a very
attractive person

00:14:10.610 --> 00:14:12.650 align:middle line:84%
because you're turned on
by something very big.

00:14:12.650 --> 00:14:15.640 align:middle line:84%
And then people want to know,
man what's lighting you up,

00:14:15.640 --> 00:14:18.680 align:middle line:84%
what's turning you on, why
you so inspired all the time?

00:14:18.680 --> 00:14:19.800 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right, right.

00:14:19.800 --> 00:14:21.758 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: It makes you a
very attractive person.

00:14:21.758 --> 00:14:25.860 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What also makes the
other, maybe a negative source

00:14:25.860 --> 00:14:27.180 align:middle line:90%
not stick to you?

00:14:27.180 --> 00:14:29.310 align:middle line:84%
And you're kind
of a Teflon figure

00:14:29.310 --> 00:14:33.470 align:middle line:84%
to that type of
negativity or depression,

00:14:33.470 --> 00:14:37.790 align:middle line:84%
because you hold that space
that's creatively inspired.

00:14:37.790 --> 00:14:40.240 align:middle line:84%
And we talked earlier
about creative stress--

00:14:40.240 --> 00:14:42.930 align:middle line:84%
this is an amazing
reframe for me,

00:14:42.930 --> 00:14:46.180 align:middle line:84%
is to look at stress in
a totally different way.

00:14:46.180 --> 00:14:48.780 align:middle line:84%
To find something that
is, as you said it,

00:14:48.780 --> 00:14:51.854 align:middle line:84%
taps into our creation
of our universe,

00:14:51.854 --> 00:14:53.270 align:middle line:84%
and then that was
creative stress.

00:14:53.270 --> 00:14:55.645 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well the whole idea
is that the creative process

00:14:55.645 --> 00:14:58.500 align:middle line:84%
is full of what I call
evolutionary tension.

00:14:58.500 --> 00:15:01.040 align:middle line:84%
So when the universe was
created, when the universe came

00:15:01.040 --> 00:15:03.250 align:middle line:84%
into being, it wasn't
a peaceful event.

00:15:03.250 --> 00:15:06.320 align:middle line:90%
It was a cosmic explosion.

00:15:06.320 --> 00:15:08.200 align:middle line:84%
Planets had to collide
into each other

00:15:08.200 --> 00:15:09.870 align:middle line:84%
to create more
complex compounds that

00:15:09.870 --> 00:15:12.660 align:middle line:84%
would make it possible
for life to emerge.

00:15:12.660 --> 00:15:14.550 align:middle line:84%
When we create
life, lovemaking is

00:15:14.550 --> 00:15:16.370 align:middle line:90%
made through creative friction.

00:15:16.370 --> 00:15:19.900 align:middle line:84%
When culture is created, when
philosophers come together

00:15:19.900 --> 00:15:22.740 align:middle line:84%
to discuss big ideas,
there's a creative friction

00:15:22.740 --> 00:15:24.190 align:middle line:90%
at the level of mind.

00:15:24.190 --> 00:15:28.040 align:middle line:84%
So creative friction,
which is the experience

00:15:28.040 --> 00:15:31.130 align:middle line:84%
of positive stress, is an
inherently positive thing.

00:15:31.130 --> 00:15:33.900 align:middle line:84%
And I think that with
the negative stress

00:15:33.900 --> 00:15:36.140 align:middle line:84%
that a lot of people
experience, which

00:15:36.140 --> 00:15:37.970 align:middle line:84%
is very common
these days, is when

00:15:37.970 --> 00:15:41.230 align:middle line:84%
we feel deeply consciously and
unconsciously deeply divided

00:15:41.230 --> 00:15:43.670 align:middle line:84%
about whether we
really want to be here.

00:15:43.670 --> 00:15:47.025 align:middle line:84%
Whether we're confused
about the relation

00:15:47.025 --> 00:15:48.650 align:middle line:84%
to existential
questions, whether life

00:15:48.650 --> 00:15:50.350 align:middle line:90%
is good, whether it's positive.

00:15:50.350 --> 00:15:52.990 align:middle line:84%
When we feel deeply ambivalent,
knowingly or unknowingly,

00:15:52.990 --> 00:15:56.130 align:middle line:84%
about being here we feel
overwhelmed by the stress

00:15:56.130 --> 00:15:57.190 align:middle line:90%
of existence.

00:15:57.190 --> 00:16:01.151 align:middle line:84%
But when we feel absolutely
free from ambiguity and free

00:16:01.151 --> 00:16:02.650 align:middle line:84%
from division about
being here we're

00:16:02.650 --> 00:16:05.630 align:middle line:84%
sure we want to be here in
this body, in this mind,

00:16:05.630 --> 00:16:07.810 align:middle line:84%
as ourselves because we
want to do everything

00:16:07.810 --> 00:16:09.460 align:middle line:84%
we can do to
wholeheartedly contribute

00:16:09.460 --> 00:16:11.660 align:middle line:84%
to the evolutionary process
and where we're going.

00:16:11.660 --> 00:16:15.110 align:middle line:84%
The stress we experience is
that positive creative friction

00:16:15.110 --> 00:16:16.370 align:middle line:90%
and we thrive on it.

00:16:16.370 --> 00:16:17.770 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Mhm, interesting.

00:16:17.770 --> 00:16:19.395 align:middle line:84%
It's definitely a
different perspective

00:16:19.395 --> 00:16:22.084 align:middle line:84%
from the debilitating
stress and looking at it

00:16:22.084 --> 00:16:23.250 align:middle line:90%
as something that stops you.

00:16:23.250 --> 00:16:25.000 align:middle line:84%
That type of stress
you're talking about--

00:16:25.000 --> 00:16:29.230 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: If we're resisting
life, if we're consciously

00:16:29.230 --> 00:16:31.460 align:middle line:84%
or unconsciously
resisting and holding away

00:16:31.460 --> 00:16:33.960 align:middle line:84%
the overwhelming reality of the
fact that we're already here

00:16:33.960 --> 00:16:36.490 align:middle line:84%
and we've got to get with it
because the time's already up,

00:16:36.490 --> 00:16:38.980 align:middle line:84%
then we're going to experience
it as very negative and very

00:16:38.980 --> 00:16:41.217 align:middle line:84%
unpleasant and we're going
to want to escape from it.

00:16:41.217 --> 00:16:42.800 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Many of our
Facebook questions

00:16:42.800 --> 00:16:44.310 align:middle line:84%
that come in
constantly are talking

00:16:44.310 --> 00:16:45.980 align:middle line:90%
about what is my purpose?

00:16:45.980 --> 00:16:49.510 align:middle line:84%
And I'm sure you have been asked
that question a million times.

00:16:49.510 --> 00:16:51.730 align:middle line:84%
But it's not what
is the purpose,

00:16:51.730 --> 00:16:55.460 align:middle line:84%
but how do you experience
that sense of purpose

00:16:55.460 --> 00:16:57.830 align:middle line:84%
while you're seeking whatever
it is you're seeking?

00:16:57.830 --> 00:16:59.830 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: I think the
question is a lot of people

00:16:59.830 --> 00:17:01.163 align:middle line:90%
want to know what my purpose is.

00:17:01.163 --> 00:17:03.580 align:middle line:84%
But my response to the
question is, well, I

00:17:03.580 --> 00:17:05.900 align:middle line:84%
think first you want to
find out who you really

00:17:05.900 --> 00:17:08.800 align:middle line:84%
are before you find out
what your purpose is.

00:17:08.800 --> 00:17:12.290 align:middle line:84%
Because I believe that when
we find out who we really are,

00:17:12.290 --> 00:17:15.180 align:middle line:84%
we simultaneously discover
what our purposes is.

00:17:15.180 --> 00:17:19.410 align:middle line:84%
So from an evolutionary
perspective, who I am

00:17:19.410 --> 00:17:22.709 align:middle line:84%
and who you are, beyond
the relative appearances

00:17:22.709 --> 00:17:25.599 align:middle line:84%
of a male body, a
female body, you know,

00:17:25.599 --> 00:17:28.020 align:middle line:84%
Andrew's personality
and Lisa's personality--

00:17:28.020 --> 00:17:30.852 align:middle line:84%
we're both equally the
energy and intelligence

00:17:30.852 --> 00:17:32.560 align:middle line:84%
that created the
universe and is creating

00:17:32.560 --> 00:17:35.740 align:middle line:84%
the universe in the form of
Lisa and the form of Andrew.

00:17:35.740 --> 00:17:37.119 align:middle line:84%
So when I realized
that if I just

00:17:37.119 --> 00:17:38.410 align:middle line:90%
think of what does Andrew want?

00:17:38.410 --> 00:17:39.715 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to come
up with one answer.

00:17:39.715 --> 00:17:41.589 align:middle line:84%
And I And I think, well,
what does the energy

00:17:41.589 --> 00:17:43.780 align:middle line:84%
and intelligence that
created the universe want

00:17:43.780 --> 00:17:45.290 align:middle line:84%
in the form of
Andrew?, I'm going

00:17:45.290 --> 00:17:46.969 align:middle line:84%
to come up with a
very different answer.

00:17:46.969 --> 00:17:48.010 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That makes sense.

00:17:48.010 --> 00:17:49.676 align:middle line:84%
When you're saying
this, we are all one.

00:17:49.676 --> 00:17:52.200 align:middle line:84%
And I've always
wondered this, how can

00:17:52.200 --> 00:17:53.970 align:middle line:84%
you say that when
I don't consider

00:17:53.970 --> 00:17:56.130 align:middle line:90%
myself one with a terrorist?

00:17:56.130 --> 00:17:59.300 align:middle line:84%
And I don't consider
myself one with someone

00:17:59.300 --> 00:18:01.610 align:middle line:90%
who wants to kill a child?

00:18:01.610 --> 00:18:03.630 align:middle line:90%
How do you explain that?

00:18:03.630 --> 00:18:08.100 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, because
the positive things

00:18:08.100 --> 00:18:10.060 align:middle line:84%
and the negative
things that occur

00:18:10.060 --> 00:18:12.760 align:middle line:84%
are still all part of
one creative unfolding.

00:18:12.760 --> 00:18:14.560 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: How, how?

00:18:14.560 --> 00:18:18.420 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Because if you
stand back and you look,

00:18:18.420 --> 00:18:20.690 align:middle line:90%
it's all one process.

00:18:20.690 --> 00:18:25.164 align:middle line:84%
And good and very positive
things happen in the process,

00:18:25.164 --> 00:18:27.830 align:middle line:84%
and negative and horrible things
also happen within the process.

00:18:27.830 --> 00:18:32.080 align:middle line:84%
But the creative
process itself is one.

00:18:32.080 --> 00:18:33.860 align:middle line:84%
And that doesn't
mean that we need

00:18:33.860 --> 00:18:36.090 align:middle line:84%
to feel good about bad
things that happen.

00:18:36.090 --> 00:18:38.450 align:middle line:84%
We want to do what we
can to correct them

00:18:38.450 --> 00:18:41.590 align:middle line:84%
and to heal
woundedness, and we want

00:18:41.590 --> 00:18:43.130 align:middle line:84%
to make the world
a better place.

00:18:43.130 --> 00:18:45.830 align:middle line:84%
But the perspective
of nonduality,

00:18:45.830 --> 00:18:48.630 align:middle line:84%
the mystical insight into
the nature of reality

00:18:48.630 --> 00:18:50.440 align:middle line:90%
is it's one happening.

00:18:50.440 --> 00:18:53.450 align:middle line:84%
It's one event in which
all kinds of things happen,

00:18:53.450 --> 00:18:54.880 align:middle line:90%
both pleasant and unpleasant.

00:18:54.880 --> 00:18:57.200 align:middle line:84%
Good and evil, it's all
part of one unfolding.

00:18:57.200 --> 00:19:00.470 align:middle line:84%
But in the form
of the appearance

00:19:00.470 --> 00:19:03.640 align:middle line:84%
of a unique individual we
start taking certain positions

00:19:03.640 --> 00:19:07.820 align:middle line:90%
that we prefer good over evil.

00:19:07.820 --> 00:19:09.734 align:middle line:90%
Happiness and not suffering.

00:19:09.734 --> 00:19:10.650 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Duality again.

00:19:10.650 --> 00:19:12.220 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: But the
mystical perspective

00:19:12.220 --> 00:19:17.790 align:middle line:84%
is we see it all as part
of one unfolding process.

00:19:17.790 --> 00:19:21.580 align:middle line:84%
Like, for example, if you think
about what I was saying before,

00:19:21.580 --> 00:19:24.870 align:middle line:84%
if planets had to
collide into each other

00:19:24.870 --> 00:19:26.500 align:middle line:84%
to create more
complex compounds that

00:19:26.500 --> 00:19:28.290 align:middle line:84%
would make it possible
for life to emerge.

00:19:28.290 --> 00:19:30.750 align:middle line:84%
If we only looked at
the cosmic collision

00:19:30.750 --> 00:19:34.260 align:middle line:84%
as being a source of violence,
we would say that's bad.

00:19:34.260 --> 00:19:38.630 align:middle line:84%
But if you say, well,
that creativity also

00:19:38.630 --> 00:19:41.960 align:middle line:84%
served the evolutionary
process in the long run,

00:19:41.960 --> 00:19:45.700 align:middle line:84%
you begin to see that how
evolution unfolds is much more

00:19:45.700 --> 00:19:49.617 align:middle line:84%
complex and integrated then
we can actually imagine.

00:19:49.617 --> 00:19:50.200 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It is.

00:19:50.200 --> 00:19:52.450 align:middle line:84%
And I can understand
why this relates

00:19:52.450 --> 00:19:54.380 align:middle line:90%
to Evolutionary Enlightenment.

00:19:54.380 --> 00:19:57.570 align:middle line:84%
This gets us chunked up to
the biggest possible picture

00:19:57.570 --> 00:20:00.620 align:middle line:84%
so that we can understand
to get unstuck and get out

00:20:00.620 --> 00:20:03.940 align:middle line:84%
of our own egoic
survival, essentially.

00:20:03.940 --> 00:20:08.560 align:middle line:84%
When you have visited gurus,
or people in India who

00:20:08.560 --> 00:20:12.000 align:middle line:84%
have achieved enormous
enlightenment,

00:20:12.000 --> 00:20:17.110 align:middle line:84%
what is their way of
bringing people up

00:20:17.110 --> 00:20:20.440 align:middle line:84%
to this place of solving--
not even solving--

00:20:20.440 --> 00:20:24.280 align:middle line:84%
but basically solving
people's suffering

00:20:24.280 --> 00:20:27.210 align:middle line:84%
and pain in the world where it
comes to hunger and starvation?

00:20:27.210 --> 00:20:30.625 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: In the East, they have
a traditional-- what I call,

00:20:30.625 --> 00:20:32.750 align:middle line:84%
and the way that I look at
it, a traditional notion

00:20:32.750 --> 00:20:34.930 align:middle line:84%
of enlightenment-- they
want to awaken people

00:20:34.930 --> 00:20:37.830 align:middle line:84%
to what's called the timeless,
formless ground of being.

00:20:37.830 --> 00:20:39.480 align:middle line:84%
It's the deepest
dimension of reality,

00:20:39.480 --> 00:20:41.840 align:middle line:84%
and the deepest
dimension of the self.

00:20:41.840 --> 00:20:45.760 align:middle line:84%
And that's a place where there's
no time, in which there's

00:20:45.760 --> 00:20:47.390 align:middle line:84%
no space, in which
there's no world.

00:20:47.390 --> 00:20:50.270 align:middle line:84%
And if you enter very
deep states of meditation

00:20:50.270 --> 00:20:53.880 align:middle line:84%
we awaken to this timelessness,
to this formlessness,

00:20:53.880 --> 00:20:56.664 align:middle line:84%
to this place where
there's only being.

00:20:56.664 --> 00:20:58.830 align:middle line:84%
And it's a place where
nothing ever happened before.

00:20:58.830 --> 00:21:03.400 align:middle line:84%
It's what the Buddha called
the uncreated, the unborn.

00:21:03.400 --> 00:21:05.940 align:middle line:84%
And so if you enter into a
very deep state of meditation,

00:21:05.940 --> 00:21:08.060 align:middle line:84%
eventually everything
will disappear

00:21:08.060 --> 00:21:10.555 align:middle line:84%
and you'll experience the
freedom of timelessness.

00:21:10.555 --> 00:21:12.930 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Which is what we're
going to take a look at here.

00:21:12.930 --> 00:21:17.150 align:middle line:84%
There's a video that talks
about spiritual self-confidence,

00:21:17.150 --> 00:21:18.460 align:middle line:90%
and what that looks like.

00:21:18.460 --> 00:21:21.256 align:middle line:90%
Let's take a look.

00:21:21.256 --> 00:21:30.776 align:middle line:90%
