00:28:56.580 --> 00:28:59.254 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, the five
fundamental principles

00:28:59.254 --> 00:29:00.920 align:middle line:84%
of how to put the
teaching into practice

00:29:00.920 --> 00:29:06.860 align:middle line:84%
is the first one is
really organizing our life

00:29:06.860 --> 00:29:10.020 align:middle line:84%
around a very deep inquiry
into the question of what's

00:29:10.020 --> 00:29:12.470 align:middle line:84%
more important
than anything else?

00:29:12.470 --> 00:29:15.640 align:middle line:84%
And so I realized that the
evolution of consciousness

00:29:15.640 --> 00:29:17.280 align:middle line:84%
and the evolution
of culture was more

00:29:17.280 --> 00:29:19.500 align:middle line:84%
important than
anything else to me.

00:29:19.500 --> 00:29:22.481 align:middle line:84%
And if we realize that the
evolution of consciousness

00:29:22.481 --> 00:29:24.980 align:middle line:84%
and the evolution of culture
is more important than anything

00:29:24.980 --> 00:29:28.980 align:middle line:84%
else, we become very
focused on that.

00:29:28.980 --> 00:29:32.150 align:middle line:84%
We organize our entire life
around the whole principle

00:29:32.150 --> 00:29:33.500 align:middle line:90%
of evolution.

00:29:33.500 --> 00:29:35.980 align:middle line:84%
And evolution at the
level of culture, you see,

00:29:35.980 --> 00:29:37.020 align:middle line:90%
is very interesting.

00:29:37.020 --> 00:29:40.550 align:middle line:84%
Because many of us are
really living in the past.

00:29:40.550 --> 00:29:43.520 align:middle line:84%
Culture is our shared ideas,
our shared values, our shared

00:29:43.520 --> 00:29:44.740 align:middle line:90%
belief systems.

00:29:44.740 --> 00:29:46.789 align:middle line:84%
And when you embrace an
evolutionary worldview,

00:29:46.789 --> 00:29:48.580 align:middle line:84%
you're more interested
in where we're going

00:29:48.580 --> 00:29:51.424 align:middle line:84%
and what's possible
versus where we have been

00:29:51.424 --> 00:29:52.840 align:middle line:84%
or what other
people have told us.

00:29:52.840 --> 00:29:53.870 align:middle line:90%
We become very creative.

00:29:53.870 --> 00:29:56.610 align:middle line:90%
We become creative visionaries.

00:29:56.610 --> 00:30:00.540 align:middle line:84%
We become interested in
creating new possibilities,

00:30:00.540 --> 00:30:02.430 align:middle line:84%
not only for ourself,
but for everyone else.

00:30:02.430 --> 00:30:05.960 align:middle line:84%
We consider ourselves to be
Pathfinders, so co-creators

00:30:05.960 --> 00:30:07.882 align:middle line:84%
with other people of
where we're going,

00:30:07.882 --> 00:30:09.090 align:middle line:90%
not where we've already come.

00:30:09.090 --> 00:30:11.420 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So not paying so
much attention to history,

00:30:11.420 --> 00:30:13.930 align:middle line:84%
looking at it as milestones,
but looking forward

00:30:13.930 --> 00:30:16.000 align:middle line:84%
to creating something
out of nothing?

00:30:16.000 --> 00:30:17.100 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: No, no, no.

00:30:17.100 --> 00:30:22.700 align:middle line:84%
We can always only build on
what has already happened.

00:30:22.700 --> 00:30:26.860 align:middle line:84%
We can't wipe everything away
and go back to the beginning.

00:30:26.860 --> 00:30:29.830 align:middle line:84%
But the thing is we realize
history is not static.

00:30:29.830 --> 00:30:32.550 align:middle line:84%
And we suddenly realize
that there's not

00:30:32.550 --> 00:30:35.360 align:middle line:84%
a divine being that exists
outside the time process that's

00:30:35.360 --> 00:30:36.400 align:middle line:90%
guiding the process.

00:30:36.400 --> 00:30:37.900 align:middle line:84%
At this particular
point in history

00:30:37.900 --> 00:30:40.540 align:middle line:84%
we realize that where
we're going in the future

00:30:40.540 --> 00:30:43.300 align:middle line:84%
depends upon the choices we
make and the actions we take.

00:30:43.300 --> 00:30:47.450 align:middle line:84%
We are creating, you and I are
the energy and intelligence

00:30:47.450 --> 00:30:50.490 align:middle line:84%
that created the universe
creating the future

00:30:50.490 --> 00:30:52.330 align:middle line:90%
at the level of human culture.

00:30:52.330 --> 00:30:54.860 align:middle line:84%
And when we begin
to see that, we

00:30:54.860 --> 00:30:58.120 align:middle line:84%
awaken beyond the small
and narrow confines

00:30:58.120 --> 00:31:03.020 align:middle line:84%
of a small egoic psychological
perspective, a very personal

00:31:03.020 --> 00:31:03.810 align:middle line:90%
perspective.

00:31:03.810 --> 00:31:07.280 align:middle line:84%
And we start seeing with
big eyes into the big future

00:31:07.280 --> 00:31:12.020 align:middle line:84%
and realizing that if we're
so inspired, that it's

00:31:12.020 --> 00:31:14.920 align:middle line:84%
our obligation to do
everything we can to create it.

00:31:14.920 --> 00:31:18.910 align:middle line:84%
We feel ourselves called to live
big lives for the sake of where

00:31:18.910 --> 00:31:20.140 align:middle line:90%
we're all going together.

00:31:20.140 --> 00:31:23.024 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So the first tenet
being the Power of Intention.

00:31:23.024 --> 00:31:24.440 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: The
intention to do that.

00:31:24.440 --> 00:31:27.590 align:middle line:84%
The intention to live
our life in relationship

00:31:27.590 --> 00:31:31.320 align:middle line:84%
to do a very big
idea, to big ideas,

00:31:31.320 --> 00:31:34.430 align:middle line:84%
and to absolute
spiritual principles.

00:31:34.430 --> 00:31:39.210 align:middle line:84%
It's the opposite of a very
small, very personalized

00:31:39.210 --> 00:31:43.240 align:middle line:84%
worldview in relationship
to just my life.

00:31:43.240 --> 00:31:47.020 align:middle line:84%
We live our life in relationship
to cosmic evolution,

00:31:47.020 --> 00:31:49.430 align:middle line:84%
to biological evolution,
to cultural evolution.

00:31:49.430 --> 00:31:52.300 align:middle line:84%
We see our life as
the leading edge

00:31:52.300 --> 00:31:55.270 align:middle line:84%
of the whole process
right here and right now.

00:31:55.270 --> 00:31:58.290 align:middle line:84%
And so we become very concerned
with where we're all going.

00:31:58.290 --> 00:32:01.390 align:middle line:84%
Where we're all going depends
upon me, it depends upon you.

00:32:01.390 --> 00:32:04.090 align:middle line:84%
So I don't really have
time not to pay attention,

00:32:04.090 --> 00:32:05.975 align:middle line:84%
and not to care about
where we're going

00:32:05.975 --> 00:32:07.350 align:middle line:84%
and how we're
going to get there.

00:32:07.350 --> 00:32:09.170 align:middle line:84%
And it's important to make a
distinction, a lot of people

00:32:09.170 --> 00:32:10.295 align:middle line:90%
are worried about survival.

00:32:10.295 --> 00:32:12.470 align:middle line:84%
How are we going to
survive global warming?

00:32:12.470 --> 00:32:14.640 align:middle line:84%
How are we going to survive
the economic crisis?

00:32:14.640 --> 00:32:16.330 align:middle line:84%
And those are
important questions,

00:32:16.330 --> 00:32:19.520 align:middle line:84%
but even if-- just to
imagine for a moment

00:32:19.520 --> 00:32:21.090 align:middle line:84%
that the crisis
of global warming

00:32:21.090 --> 00:32:24.930 align:middle line:84%
was somehow magically solved,
and even imagine for a moment

00:32:24.930 --> 00:32:27.720 align:middle line:84%
that our economic crisis was
solved-- in terms of where

00:32:27.720 --> 00:32:30.300 align:middle line:84%
we're all going at the level
of culture and shared values,

00:32:30.300 --> 00:32:32.550 align:middle line:84%
that question wouldn't
have been answered yet.

00:32:32.550 --> 00:32:34.950 align:middle line:84%
So some of us have to
be concerned not just

00:32:34.950 --> 00:32:37.360 align:middle line:84%
about survival-- how are
we going to survive--

00:32:37.360 --> 00:32:38.950 align:middle line:84%
but how are we actually
going to evolve and develop

00:32:38.950 --> 00:32:39.800 align:middle line:90%
at the level of culture?

00:32:39.800 --> 00:32:41.930 align:middle line:84%
And that's a very big and
very exciting question.

00:32:41.930 --> 00:32:44.460 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: A very exciting
question is a key point to that.

00:32:44.460 --> 00:32:46.820 align:middle line:84%
It is very exciting to
go into that direction.

00:32:46.820 --> 00:32:48.320 align:middle line:84%
And that takes us
to the next tenet,

00:32:48.320 --> 00:32:51.280 align:middle line:84%
which is that volition,
that power of volition

00:32:51.280 --> 00:32:52.120 align:middle line:90%
moving forward.

00:32:52.120 --> 00:32:54.450 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well the Law of
Volition is all about choices.

00:32:54.450 --> 00:32:57.820 align:middle line:84%
And in other words,
if we want to be

00:32:57.820 --> 00:32:59.800 align:middle line:84%
a spiritually
liberated individual

00:32:59.800 --> 00:33:01.966 align:middle line:84%
we have to come to that
point in our own development

00:33:01.966 --> 00:33:05.270 align:middle line:84%
where we stop blaming anybody
else for our predicament.

00:33:05.270 --> 00:33:10.400 align:middle line:84%
We cease to experience
ourselves as being victims.

00:33:10.400 --> 00:33:12.650 align:middle line:84%
Everybody who's been
born has, in some way,

00:33:12.650 --> 00:33:14.310 align:middle line:84%
been hurt, and wounded,
and traumatized

00:33:14.310 --> 00:33:16.360 align:middle line:90%
by another or others.

00:33:16.360 --> 00:33:21.016 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes it's
obviously more than others.

00:33:21.016 --> 00:33:22.390 align:middle line:84%
But if we want to
be free we have

00:33:22.390 --> 00:33:24.848 align:middle line:84%
to accept responsibility for
the consequences of everything

00:33:24.848 --> 00:33:27.100 align:middle line:84%
that's ever happened
to us and realize

00:33:27.100 --> 00:33:29.140 align:middle line:90%
it's all my own predicament.

00:33:29.140 --> 00:33:32.500 align:middle line:84%
We take full responsibility
for our own karmic predicament.

00:33:32.500 --> 00:33:34.260 align:middle line:84%
It's my problem, it's
not anybody else's.

00:33:34.260 --> 00:33:36.480 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Goodness, explain that.

00:33:36.480 --> 00:33:39.750 align:middle line:84%
You taking full responsibility
for your karmic predicament.

00:33:39.750 --> 00:33:41.890 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, because
our karmic predicament

00:33:41.890 --> 00:33:43.050 align:middle line:90%
tends to be very complex.

00:33:43.050 --> 00:33:46.140 align:middle line:84%
Because who we are is
we're very complex beings.

00:33:46.140 --> 00:33:49.220 align:middle line:84%
We're all a product of--
there's biological history.

00:33:49.220 --> 00:33:51.000 align:middle line:84%
There's my personal
family history.

00:33:51.000 --> 00:33:52.830 align:middle line:84%
I'm Jewish, so
part of my history

00:33:52.830 --> 00:33:55.510 align:middle line:84%
has to do with my
ethnic background.

00:33:55.510 --> 00:33:57.390 align:middle line:84%
And there's so many
other dimensions

00:33:57.390 --> 00:33:59.580 align:middle line:84%
of all the different
ways we're conditioned.

00:33:59.580 --> 00:34:03.750 align:middle line:84%
So there's a lot that we have
to be responsible for if we want

00:34:03.750 --> 00:34:06.620 align:middle line:84%
to be able to become
masters of our own destiny.

00:34:06.620 --> 00:34:09.219 align:middle line:84%
Instead of being
victims of history

00:34:09.219 --> 00:34:12.030 align:middle line:84%
we want to become masters
of our own destiny.

00:34:12.030 --> 00:34:13.810 align:middle line:84%
In order to do
that, we have to be

00:34:13.810 --> 00:34:17.330 align:middle line:84%
willing to heroically take
complete responsibility

00:34:17.330 --> 00:34:20.679 align:middle line:84%
for everything that's made
us the person we are now,

00:34:20.679 --> 00:34:24.950 align:middle line:84%
and then decide who we want to
be and make those choices that

00:34:24.950 --> 00:34:28.290 align:middle line:84%
will make it possible for
us to become that person.

00:34:28.290 --> 00:34:30.496 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So basically taking
complete responsibility

00:34:30.496 --> 00:34:32.870 align:middle line:84%
for everything that's ever
happened to us and moving onto

00:34:32.870 --> 00:34:33.429 align:middle line:90%
the next--

00:34:33.429 --> 00:34:35.969 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: Endeavour to do that.

00:34:35.969 --> 00:34:37.454 align:middle line:90%
It's a heroic aspiration.

00:34:37.454 --> 00:34:38.620 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's a whole show.

00:34:38.620 --> 00:34:43.159 align:middle line:90%


00:34:43.159 --> 00:34:46.850 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: It's being
willing to nobly embrace

00:34:46.850 --> 00:34:48.280 align:middle line:90%
the totality of our being.

00:34:48.280 --> 00:34:51.600 align:middle line:84%
And we will often
fail doing so, but we

00:34:51.600 --> 00:34:54.719 align:middle line:84%
need to at least try to take
that much responsibility

00:34:54.719 --> 00:34:59.337 align:middle line:84%
for who we are, and how we
are, and who we want to be.

00:34:59.337 --> 00:35:00.920 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I like how
you move it forward

00:35:00.920 --> 00:35:04.670 align:middle line:84%
and not getting stuck
into that place of pain,

00:35:04.670 --> 00:35:05.680 align:middle line:90%
but moving forward.

00:35:05.680 --> 00:35:07.390 align:middle line:90%
So that will then take us--

00:35:07.390 --> 00:35:09.140 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, an
evolutionary orientation

00:35:09.140 --> 00:35:11.810 align:middle line:84%
is always about what can
be, never about what is.

00:35:11.810 --> 00:35:14.690 align:middle line:84%
An evolutionary orientation
is always about what can be,

00:35:14.690 --> 00:35:15.660 align:middle line:90%
never about what is.

00:35:15.660 --> 00:35:18.570 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So it's not so much
about the power of now,

00:35:18.570 --> 00:35:20.310 align:middle line:84%
being in this
moment, present time?

00:35:20.310 --> 00:35:22.792 align:middle line:90%
It's more about the next moment?

00:35:22.792 --> 00:35:25.000 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: In what I call the
traditional enlightenment

00:35:25.000 --> 00:35:27.440 align:middle line:84%
is about being in
the present moment.

00:35:27.440 --> 00:35:31.120 align:middle line:84%
In an evolutionary orientation
to liberation and to life,

00:35:31.120 --> 00:35:33.030 align:middle line:84%
it's always about
the next moment.

00:35:33.030 --> 00:35:35.800 align:middle line:84%
Because in a sense, the
present moment is already here.

00:35:35.800 --> 00:35:39.520 align:middle line:84%
We've always already
arrived in the present.

00:35:39.520 --> 00:35:42.880 align:middle line:84%
And so therefore, we can't
really change anything now,

00:35:42.880 --> 00:35:45.390 align:middle line:84%
but we can affect change in
what hasn't happened yet.

00:35:45.390 --> 00:35:46.890 align:middle line:84%
And that's why in
this orientation

00:35:46.890 --> 00:35:48.749 align:middle line:84%
it's always, always
future-oriented.

00:35:48.749 --> 00:35:50.540 align:middle line:84%
Because that's the
place, through volition,

00:35:50.540 --> 00:35:52.780 align:middle line:90%
we can actually affect change.

00:35:52.780 --> 00:35:55.630 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: The next tenet, I see,
is more about authenticity.

00:35:55.630 --> 00:35:57.230 align:middle line:84%
I find this a very
interesting one.

00:35:57.230 --> 00:35:57.770 align:middle line:90%
What is it?

00:35:57.770 --> 00:36:00.770 align:middle line:84%
It is Face Everything
and Avoid Nothing.

00:36:00.770 --> 00:36:03.340 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well facing everything,
avoiding nothing is, I feel,

00:36:03.340 --> 00:36:05.830 align:middle line:84%
the most challenging, and
really the highest and most

00:36:05.830 --> 00:36:08.540 align:middle line:84%
profound form of
spiritual practice, which

00:36:08.540 --> 00:36:10.350 align:middle line:90%
is the practice of awareness.

00:36:10.350 --> 00:36:14.390 align:middle line:84%
And the practice of awareness
in all the great enlightenment

00:36:14.390 --> 00:36:17.690 align:middle line:84%
traditions is really the way
to become an enlightened person

00:36:17.690 --> 00:36:22.720 align:middle line:84%
is through the choice, or making
the effort to be more aware.

00:36:22.720 --> 00:36:27.560 align:middle line:84%
And so we can say, well,
most of us face very little

00:36:27.560 --> 00:36:28.770 align:middle line:90%
and avoid a lot.

00:36:28.770 --> 00:36:30.850 align:middle line:84%
Or face nothing and
avoid everything.

00:36:30.850 --> 00:36:32.590 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Why do we do that?

00:36:32.590 --> 00:36:35.990 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Because
reality is hard to take.

00:36:35.990 --> 00:36:40.010 align:middle line:84%
And because we have the images
about who we are and often

00:36:40.010 --> 00:36:42.200 align:middle line:84%
they're very different
from how we actually are.

00:36:42.200 --> 00:36:44.420 align:middle line:84%
And because we tend to
be very, very sensitive,

00:36:44.420 --> 00:36:45.280 align:middle line:90%
very narcissistic.

00:36:45.280 --> 00:36:47.480 align:middle line:84%
We often can't, we
find it unbearable

00:36:47.480 --> 00:36:50.825 align:middle line:90%
to see ourselves more clearly.

00:36:50.825 --> 00:36:54.240 align:middle line:84%
And of course, if you want to
be free and you want to evolve,

00:36:54.240 --> 00:36:56.430 align:middle line:84%
if you want to
continue to develop,

00:36:56.430 --> 00:36:58.430 align:middle line:84%
we're not so afraid
of seeing the truth

00:36:58.430 --> 00:37:01.860 align:middle line:84%
because we don't want to
remain simply as we are now.

00:37:01.860 --> 00:37:04.170 align:middle line:84%
We're constantly
striving to evolve

00:37:04.170 --> 00:37:06.850 align:middle line:84%
to become more of
who we could be.

00:37:06.850 --> 00:37:08.460 align:middle line:84%
And so in order to
do that, we have

00:37:08.460 --> 00:37:10.170 align:middle line:90%
to remove all the obstacles.

00:37:10.170 --> 00:37:11.760 align:middle line:84%
And one of the
fundamental obstacles

00:37:11.760 --> 00:37:15.000 align:middle line:84%
is we're unconscious
of our motivations.

00:37:15.000 --> 00:37:17.620 align:middle line:84%
Often the left hand doesn't know
what the right hand is doing.

00:37:17.620 --> 00:37:19.800 align:middle line:84%
So we want to become
very conscious

00:37:19.800 --> 00:37:22.384 align:middle line:84%
of what's making us tick, of why
we're doing what we're doing.

00:37:22.384 --> 00:37:24.341 align:middle line:84%
Why we're making the
choices that we're making.

00:37:24.341 --> 00:37:26.950 align:middle line:84%
In order to do that, we have to
be willing to make the effort

00:37:26.950 --> 00:37:31.260 align:middle line:84%
to become a lot more
conscious than we tend to be.

00:37:31.260 --> 00:37:34.355 align:middle line:84%
But in this case, we're
going to remove the obstacles

00:37:34.355 --> 00:37:36.570 align:middle line:90%
to our own potential to evolve.

00:37:36.570 --> 00:37:40.710 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So if we face
everything and avoid nothing,

00:37:40.710 --> 00:37:42.850 align:middle line:90%
does that get rid of judgment?

00:37:42.850 --> 00:37:48.352 align:middle line:84%
Is judgment considered
avoidance, basically?

00:37:48.352 --> 00:37:50.810 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, it all depends
on what you mean by judgment.

00:37:50.810 --> 00:37:54.310 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I think that a big
part of higher development

00:37:54.310 --> 00:37:56.780 align:middle line:90%
is learning how to discriminate.

00:37:56.780 --> 00:37:58.900 align:middle line:84%
Intelligent
discrimination, learning

00:37:58.900 --> 00:38:00.360 align:middle line:90%
how to make distinctions.

00:38:00.360 --> 00:38:03.850 align:middle line:84%
So some people think if you make
any distinctions between one

00:38:03.850 --> 00:38:05.910 align:middle line:84%
individual and another,
one quality and another,

00:38:05.910 --> 00:38:08.060 align:middle line:84%
if you make value
judgments, they

00:38:08.060 --> 00:38:10.220 align:middle line:84%
feel there's something
unspiritual or something

00:38:10.220 --> 00:38:12.280 align:middle line:90%
inherently negative about it.

00:38:12.280 --> 00:38:14.590 align:middle line:84%
But I don't actually
think that's true.

00:38:14.590 --> 00:38:16.720 align:middle line:84%
Part of higher
development is learning

00:38:16.720 --> 00:38:18.221 align:middle line:84%
discernment, the
art of discernment.

00:38:18.221 --> 00:38:20.428 align:middle line:84%
And so if we're going to
learn the art of discernment

00:38:20.428 --> 00:38:22.140 align:middle line:90%
we have to make value judgments.

00:38:22.140 --> 00:38:25.880 align:middle line:84%
And that's a big part, I
think, of higher development.

00:38:25.880 --> 00:38:29.690 align:middle line:84%
So I think learning how to
make accurate and truthful

00:38:29.690 --> 00:38:34.700 align:middle line:84%
judgments, or
value distinctions,

00:38:34.700 --> 00:38:36.200 align:middle line:84%
is a big part of
higher development.

00:38:36.200 --> 00:38:37.908 align:middle line:84%
I think that's something
we have to learn

00:38:37.908 --> 00:38:41.046 align:middle line:84%
how to do with greater and
greater degrees of accuracy,

00:38:41.046 --> 00:38:42.170 align:middle line:90%
and precision, and insight.

00:38:42.170 --> 00:38:44.190 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Can you give
me an example of that?

00:38:44.190 --> 00:38:49.030 align:middle line:84%
How do you, in your live, face
everything and avoid nothing?

00:38:49.030 --> 00:38:51.350 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, to
be-- I don't think

00:38:51.350 --> 00:38:54.400 align:middle line:84%
it's possible to face
everything and avoid nothing,

00:38:54.400 --> 00:38:58.037 align:middle line:84%
but we want to strive to face
everything and avoid nothing.

00:38:58.037 --> 00:39:00.570 align:middle line:90%


00:39:00.570 --> 00:39:05.040 align:middle line:84%
And we want to do
that because evolution

00:39:05.040 --> 00:39:07.400 align:middle line:90%
is about development in time.

00:39:07.400 --> 00:39:09.620 align:middle line:84%
So in this particular
lifetime, we only

00:39:09.620 --> 00:39:12.140 align:middle line:84%
have a certain amount of
time to evolve and develop.

00:39:12.140 --> 00:39:14.850 align:middle line:84%
So we want to use
the time we have

00:39:14.850 --> 00:39:16.730 align:middle line:84%
in the most productive
manner possible.

00:39:16.730 --> 00:39:18.820 align:middle line:84%
We don't want to waste
time, because time

00:39:18.820 --> 00:39:21.330 align:middle line:84%
is all we have from an
evolutionary point of view.

00:39:21.330 --> 00:39:23.690 align:middle line:84%
So therefore, we want to
be very aware of what we're

00:39:23.690 --> 00:39:26.460 align:middle line:84%
doing, what's motivating us to
make the choices that we make,

00:39:26.460 --> 00:39:29.190 align:middle line:84%
so that we can be sure that
the choices that we make

00:39:29.190 --> 00:39:33.050 align:middle line:84%
are in alignment with our
highest ideals and aspirations.

00:39:33.050 --> 00:39:34.800 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I see, that
makes it connect.

00:39:34.800 --> 00:39:37.340 align:middle line:84%
That completely connects it
to the power of volition,

00:39:37.340 --> 00:39:39.250 align:middle line:90%
and therefore, the intention.

00:39:39.250 --> 00:39:41.660 align:middle line:84%
All right, so the next
tenet that you talk about--

00:39:41.660 --> 00:39:42.620 align:middle line:90%
and these are tenets.

00:39:42.620 --> 00:39:44.467 align:middle line:90%
Tenets are just guidelines.

00:39:44.467 --> 00:39:46.800 align:middle line:84%
These are things that you're
striving and achieving to--

00:39:46.800 --> 00:39:52.187 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, it's a
spiritual context for living.

00:39:52.187 --> 00:39:54.520 align:middle line:84%
Because a lot of, what's the
context in which most of us

00:39:54.520 --> 00:39:54.870 align:middle line:90%
are living?

00:39:54.870 --> 00:39:55.985 align:middle line:84%
They say, well, I
don't really know.

00:39:55.985 --> 00:39:58.193 align:middle line:84%
It's just kind of I want
this, and I don't want that.

00:39:58.193 --> 00:40:00.870 align:middle line:84%
I said, I know but what's
the context, the picture,

00:40:00.870 --> 00:40:02.960 align:middle line:84%
the big picture in which
your life is lived?

00:40:02.960 --> 00:40:05.295 align:middle line:84%
For example, when
people are members

00:40:05.295 --> 00:40:07.979 align:middle line:84%
of some of the great mythic
religious traditions,

00:40:07.979 --> 00:40:09.020 align:middle line:90%
there's a meta narrative.

00:40:09.020 --> 00:40:10.890 align:middle line:84%
There's a big picture
which frames and helps

00:40:10.890 --> 00:40:13.020 align:middle line:84%
to orient life and
the way it's lived.

00:40:13.020 --> 00:40:16.180 align:middle line:84%
But for those of us who grew up
in a secular culture, a secular

00:40:16.180 --> 00:40:18.910 align:middle line:84%
context, we haven't been
given these big meta

00:40:18.910 --> 00:40:22.120 align:middle line:84%
narratives in which
to frame our lives.

00:40:22.120 --> 00:40:24.270 align:middle line:84%
And unfortunately
for us, it's really

00:40:24.270 --> 00:40:26.690 align:middle line:84%
come down to what's going
to make me feel good?

00:40:26.690 --> 00:40:27.990 align:middle line:90%
Life is all about me.

00:40:27.990 --> 00:40:32.000 align:middle line:84%
There's no moral, philosophical,
or spiritual context for life.

00:40:32.000 --> 00:40:34.720 align:middle line:84%
And it tends to make
getting somewhere big

00:40:34.720 --> 00:40:36.300 align:middle line:90%
and profound very difficult.

00:40:36.300 --> 00:40:39.150 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It takes the what's
in it for me out of it.

00:40:39.150 --> 00:40:40.320 align:middle line:90%
Very interesting.

00:40:40.320 --> 00:40:43.397 align:middle line:84%
So the Process Perspective
is the fourth tenet.

00:40:43.397 --> 00:40:44.980 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, the
Process Perspective

00:40:44.980 --> 00:40:47.621 align:middle line:84%
is a very big part of an
evolutionary orientation

00:40:47.621 --> 00:40:48.120 align:middle line:90%
to life.

00:40:48.120 --> 00:40:51.470 align:middle line:84%
Because once again,
we're all part

00:40:51.470 --> 00:40:54.150 align:middle line:84%
of a cosmic process that
had a beginning in time

00:40:54.150 --> 00:40:55.770 align:middle line:90%
14 billion years ago.

00:40:55.770 --> 00:40:58.795 align:middle line:84%
And so we want to understand
that when there was the Big

00:40:58.795 --> 00:41:02.280 align:middle line:84%
Bang, there was a big cosmic
explosion of energy and light,

00:41:02.280 --> 00:41:05.670 align:middle line:90%
and matter emerged from nothing.

00:41:05.670 --> 00:41:10.910 align:middle line:84%
And then miraculously,
from energy and matter,

00:41:10.910 --> 00:41:12.980 align:middle line:90%
life emerged.

00:41:12.980 --> 00:41:15.670 align:middle line:84%
And from life, eventually,
human consciousness

00:41:15.670 --> 00:41:17.120 align:middle line:90%
and human culture.

00:41:17.120 --> 00:41:19.670 align:middle line:84%
So when we realize
that, we realize

00:41:19.670 --> 00:41:22.980 align:middle line:84%
that my capacity for
consciousness, and cognition,

00:41:22.980 --> 00:41:27.240 align:middle line:84%
and thought, and subjectivity,
and self-reflective awareness

00:41:27.240 --> 00:41:30.380 align:middle line:84%
is the product of this deep
time developmental processes,

00:41:30.380 --> 00:41:35.100 align:middle line:84%
I realize that my
body, that my mind,

00:41:35.100 --> 00:41:40.150 align:middle line:84%
and my personality has all been
created by this cosmic process,

00:41:40.150 --> 00:41:43.090 align:middle line:84%
by this biological process,
by this cultural process.

00:41:43.090 --> 00:41:45.370 align:middle line:84%
It's one process, they're
not many processes

00:41:45.370 --> 00:41:46.430 align:middle line:90%
from this perspective.

00:41:46.430 --> 00:41:48.950 align:middle line:84%
There's one process
that has given rise,

00:41:48.950 --> 00:41:51.000 align:middle line:84%
and is giving rise
to all of this.

00:41:51.000 --> 00:41:54.030 align:middle line:84%
And when you see that, you
begin to take your own life

00:41:54.030 --> 00:41:55.340 align:middle line:90%
less personally.

00:41:55.340 --> 00:42:00.726 align:middle line:84%
You begin to see the
process in everything.

00:42:00.726 --> 00:42:02.350 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's the
Process Perspective.

00:42:02.350 --> 00:42:05.630 align:middle line:84%
The process of evolution that
we have gone through and that--

00:42:05.630 --> 00:42:07.980 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: You see every aspect
of your own personal life,

00:42:07.980 --> 00:42:11.090 align:middle line:84%
and of everything that's
happening in the world,

00:42:11.090 --> 00:42:13.570 align:middle line:84%
as a product of a
cosmic unfolding.

00:42:13.570 --> 00:42:17.940 align:middle line:84%
Not as discreet as the
discrete personal event,

00:42:17.940 --> 00:42:19.810 align:middle line:84%
or as some isolated
cultural event.

00:42:19.810 --> 00:42:23.289 align:middle line:84%
But you see everything is in
one way or another related

00:42:23.289 --> 00:42:24.080 align:middle line:90%
to everything else.

00:42:24.080 --> 00:42:26.180 align:middle line:84%
It's what they say
in Mahayana Buddhism,

00:42:26.180 --> 00:42:28.925 align:middle line:84%
it's similar with the law
of dependent origination.

00:42:28.925 --> 00:42:31.050 align:middle line:84%
Everything that exists
depends upon everything else

00:42:31.050 --> 00:42:33.250 align:middle line:90%
that exists.

00:42:33.250 --> 00:42:37.340 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So this is basically
taking this nonduality theme

00:42:37.340 --> 00:42:40.470 align:middle line:84%
again and saying that
we are not separate.

00:42:40.470 --> 00:42:45.990 align:middle line:84%
Don't take what we have, our own
experience personally-- which

00:42:45.990 --> 00:42:50.050 align:middle line:84%
I absolutely love-- and see
everything as evolutionary.

00:42:50.050 --> 00:42:51.660 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well,
it's true through.

00:42:51.660 --> 00:42:53.900 align:middle line:84%
I mean, everything
that you could see

00:42:53.900 --> 00:42:57.430 align:middle line:84%
and everything you can
see, taste, smell, touch,

00:42:57.430 --> 00:43:01.790 align:middle line:84%
and imagination is all
part of this one process

00:43:01.790 --> 00:43:04.350 align:middle line:84%
that's unfolding and
that's going somewhere.

00:43:04.350 --> 00:43:06.980 align:middle line:84%
And so when you
realize that and you

00:43:06.980 --> 00:43:10.230 align:middle line:84%
realize that nothing
is separate and there

00:43:10.230 --> 00:43:12.340 align:middle line:84%
is no such thing as
anything being separate,

00:43:12.340 --> 00:43:15.130 align:middle line:90%
it liberates you from your ego.

00:43:15.130 --> 00:43:17.390 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So some of our
Facebook questions coming in,

00:43:17.390 --> 00:43:20.680 align:middle line:84%
